The Treasury’s return to the bond market marks the beginning of a new phase of macroeconomic stability — one in which capital will gradually flow back toward real, yield-generating assets. If Europe maintains its current balance between price control and growth, Spain’s real estate sector could continue to benefit from this period of financial calm, consolidating its position as one of the most resilient pillars of the national economy.

